<package name="python-pytest-recording" project="openSUSE:Factory">
  <title>A pytest plugin that allows you recording of network interactions via VCRpy</title>
  <description>A pytest plugin that records network interactions in your tests
via VCR.py.

Features
 * Straightforward `pytest.mark.vcr`, that reflects
   `VCR.use_cassettes` API;
 * Combining multiple VCR cassettes
 * Network access blocking;
 * The `rewrite` recording mode that rewrites cassettes
   from scratch.</description>
  <devel project="devel:languages:python:pytest" package="python-pytest-recording"/>
  <url>https://github.com/kiwicom/pytest-recording</url>
</package>
